      <guid>https://conflictednerd.github.io/blog/introduction-to-optimization/</guid>
      <description>Optimization: An Introduction (Based on a lecture by professor Coralia Cartis, university of Oxford)
This short note is mainly about optimization problems; more specifically, non-convex optimization problems. Generally, different approaches to solving these problems can be put into three main categories:
Those that use derivatives, be it first order (gradient descent) or higher order (Newton&amp;rsquo;s method), Those that don&amp;rsquo;t use derivatives, regarded as derivative-free methods (evolutionary methods), Inexact and probabilistic methods.</description>
